<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-526-700  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 526 700.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  August 10 1989 n1176 p1(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Burton in revolt as DB2 doubts spread. (Burton Group PLC, DB2 database management system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Collins, Tony; Bicknell, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>British retailers are opting for data base management systems(DBMS) other than IBM's DB2, which they claim is too slow and apoor performer.andP;  Burton Group PLC tested DB2 for more than a yearbefore placing a 500,000 pound sterling offer with ComputerCorporation of America (CCA) for its Model 204 DBMS.andP;  CCA's 204 isthe system most often cited as a replacement for DB2.andP;  DB2'sapparent failure to impress is doubly important for IBM becausethe purchase of the DBMS usually leads to the acquisition ofsupporting software applications.andP;  If no company wants DB2, themarket for supporting software will dry up considerably.andP;  Somebusiness users who have found DB2 lacking in speed and securityconsiderations are Marks andamp; Spencer PLC, Joint Credit Card CompanyLtd, and Extel Financial.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Burton Group PLC (data processing)International Business Machines Corp. (products)Computer Corporation of America (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   DB2 (Data base management system) (usage)204 9.0 (Data base management system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsRetailingInformation Storage and Retrieval.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>